verbose_text: There is also evidence for remodeling in NPs, including an increase in glandular proliferation, increased numbers of blood vessels, an increase in alpha-SMA + myofibroblasts, and deposition of collagen types I, III, and V. XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR Several profibrotic cytokines have been found to be increased in NP, including GM-CSF, transforming growth factor beta (TGF-beta), platelet derived growth factor, fibroblast growth factor and vascular endothelial growth factor, epidermal growth factor, insulin like growth factor, and IL-11.
